.TH "get_state_synchronize_srcu" 9 "get_state_synchronize_srcu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_state_synchronize_srcu \- Provide an end-of-grace-period cookie
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" get_state_synchronize_srcu
.BI "(struct srcu_struct *ssp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
srcu_struct to provide cookie for.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns a cookie that can be passed to
\fBpoll_state_synchronize_srcu\fP, which will return true if a full grace
period has elapsed in the meantime.  It is the caller's responsibility
to make sure that grace period happens, for example, by invoking
\fBcall_srcu\fP after return from \fBget_state_synchronize_srcu\fP.
